message:
A large amount of searches are queuing on {{node_name.name}} in cluster {{es-cluster-name.name}}. This likely means that the instance is under heavy load and can't keep up with incoming search queries. This can be exacerbated by garbage collection. See [runbook](https://joinhandshake.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/DA/pages/2802843680/Troubleshooting+Elasticsearch#Alert%3A-Large-Elasticsearch-Search-Queue).

If no nodes have died recently and the cluster is reporting healthy, see https://joinhandshake.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/DA/pages/763593036/Elasticsearch+Cluster+Debugging.


